<p>Hi team,</p>

<p>We have two layout options for how the <strong>Meet the Team</strong> section is organized. Everything else on the page is identical between the two versions. Both are now mobile and iPad friendly.</p>

<h2>V4 - Stacked Sections</h2>
<p><a href="https://askit-inc.github.io/spotlight-series-microsite/#/spotlight-v4">https://askit-inc.github.io/spotlight-series-microsite/#/spotlight-v4</a></p>
<ul>
<li>Team is shown as two stacked sections on one page</li>
<li>"Meet the Team - Main Site" appears first, then "Meet the Team - Endeavor Site" below</li>
<li>User scrolls through all providers in one long list</li>
</ul>

<h2>V5 - Equal Tabs (Recommended)</h2>
<p><a href="https://askit-inc.github.io/spotlight-series-microsite/#/spotlight-v5">https://askit-inc.github.io/spotlight-series-microsite/#/spotlight-v5</a></p>
<ul>
<li>Team uses two equal tabs with institution logos: <strong>UChicago Medicine</strong> | <strong>Endeavor Health</strong></li>
<li>Tabs are visually equal - no hierarchy implied, neither site appears "above" the other</li>
<li>User clicks a tab to switch between teams (no extra scrolling)</li>
<li>Dr. Sarswat appears in both tabs since she leads across both institutions</li>
</ul>

<h2>Comparison</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Feature</th><th>V4 (Stacked)</th><th>V5 (Tabs)</th></tr>
<tr><td>Layout</td><td>Two sections, one below the other</td><td>Two equal tabs, click to switch</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hierarchy</td><td>UChicago appears first (top), Endeavor below</td><td>Equal - neither is "above" the other</td></tr>
<tr><td>Scrolling</td><td>Long page, scroll through both teams</td><td>Compact - only one team visible at a time</td></tr>
<tr><td>Branding</td><td>Text labels only</td><td>Institution logos + text</td></tr>
<tr><td>Dr. Sarswat</td><td>Listed in both sections</td><td>Listed in both tabs</td></tr>
<tr><td>Partnership signal</td><td>Could imply Endeavor is secondary</td><td>Presents as equal partners</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>Other Updates in This Build</h2>
<ul>
<li>"June 2026" now appears inline next to the program title (same size, black color for differentiation)</li>
<li>All gray subtitle text darkened for better readability</li>
<li>"Nine specialists" changed to "Nine specialties"</li>
<li>Director highlights now use checkmark icons instead of plain bullets</li>
<li>Pillar icons (heart, DNA, microscope) now inline with their titles</li>
<li>Education section uses collapsible dropdown grouped by institution</li>
<li>Responsive: mobile and iPad layouts fully working</li>
<li>Dr. Goodman removed from Endeavor listing per request</li>
</ul>

<div class="recommend">
<strong>Recommendation:</strong> V5 (Tabs) presents Endeavor as an equal partner rather than a sub-section listed below UChicago. It is cleaner, requires less scrolling, and patients can quickly find their location's team. This aligns with the "shared site" approach discussed.
</div>

<p>Please review both and let me know which direction you'd like to go with.</p>

<p>Thanks,<br>Sukh</p>

